<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69686"Target=_blank">Jonathin</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unamsundeathmonkey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Namsun DeathMonkey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 807<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/9/02 8:20:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1868.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Offhand question</span><hr size=1> I think the general rule is to put the higher dmg weapon in the offhand because you hit with the offhand less and when you hit you want it to count.  Every round you *will* attack with the weapon in your mainhand but the Dual Wield check needs to suceed before you'll attack with your offhand weapon.  Therefore if were using (random examples with the same ratio) a 11/22 weapon and a 15/30 weapon, the 15/30 should (at least imo) go in your offhand because when you hit with the offhand you'd rather get the solid hit. <p><center><IMG SRC=http://namsun.homestead.com/files/eqpics/namsunsig2.jpg><br>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=161080>Celestial Monkey</a> of the 59th Order <br>
Member of <A HREF=http://www.tkagiro.com>T`kagi Ro</A>, Fennin Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand High Poobah</span><br>  Posts: 4012<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/9/02 9:30:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1868.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Offhand question</span><hr size=1> The rule is that you want the best pure ratio of damage/delay in your offhand, because it does not get a damage bonus and is independent of the primary hand. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fopoodzo>Fopoodzo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 680<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/10/02 5:47:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1868.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Offhand question</span><hr size=1> Ratio is all that matters offhand (although that's not always true it is true most of the time).<br>
<br>
Main hand you've got to factor in ratio AND speed (for damage bonus, faster = better). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaleb123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daleb123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 286<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/10/02 7:57:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1868.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Offhand Damage</span><hr size=1> For secondary hand damage output, damage ratio is the main consideration. A faster weapon with the same ratio gives the same damage output.<br>
<br>
However, damage output itself is not the only consideration. Generally speaking, when hunting in a group, aggro management is a more important consideration. A faster weapon with the same damage output generates more hate than the slower weapon; depending on your role, this may or may not be what you want. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usoluafein.showPublicProfile?language=EN>soluafein</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/10/02 12:08:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1868.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Offhand Damage</span><hr size=1> Thank you all for the info :). I didnt even think about getting agro hehe let the tank have it. <p><center>
